'Yeah.'

535
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:37,320
Listen, I'll give you
a ring later in the week

536
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:38,920
and give you the address.

537
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:40,320
OK, then.

538
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,840
'OK. Tada, then.'

539
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:43,080
Bye-bye.

540
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:49,040
Jesus!

541
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:53,680
You should've just said yes.

542
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:56,160
Makin' me look like a... Oh!

543
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:59,200
I can hardly say no now.

544
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:00,800
That's up to you.

545
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:03,800
We don't know anything
about this person.

546
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:06,800
Some new mate. They've
been out a few times.

547
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,320
Two hysterical nutters.

548
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:10,320
I'm glad she's got a friend.

549
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:12,320
I'm gonna have a great time(!)

550
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:14,320
Thought I'd ask Jane as well.

551
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:16,840
Anybody else you want to invite?

552
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:19,360
We've only got
four garden chairs!

553
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:22,400
Oh, give us two
of them painkillers.

554
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,080
There you go.

555
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:30,680
D'you fancy some fish and chips?

556
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:32,200
Don't be sarcastic.

557
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:34,240
I wasn't. Sorry.

558
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,160
Cheers, mate.

559
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:09,960
[Knocking]

560
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:14,000
There's a bell here.

561
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:15,800
Don't. I've just done
the knocker.

562
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:17,120
All right.

563
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:19,240
Hello there.

564
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:21,360
Hello, sweetheart.

565
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,360
You got here in one piece?

566
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:24,880
Long time no see.

567
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,400
Yes. Thank you.

568
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,160
Hello, birthday girl.

569
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,680
All right, Monica?

570
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,320
- Look at you.
- This is Paul.

571
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:32,920
- Hello, Paul.
- How d'you do?

572
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:35,680
[Monica] Nice to meet you.
There's Maurice.

573
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,280
Now come away in.

574
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:42,880
- Hi, Jane.
- Hello, Monica.

575
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:49,320
This is Jane. Maurice just
picked her up from the station.

576
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:51,320
[Cynthia] Here he is!

577
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:52,720
Hello, sweetheart.

578
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:53,920
Hiya.

579
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:55,920
[Roxanne] All right, Maurice?

580
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:57,440
I got you that.

581
00:31:57,560 --> 00:32:00,960
- You didn't have to do that.
- It's all right.

582
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:02,480
This is Paul. Maurice.

583
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:03,960
All right, mate.

584
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,960
Ain't you got one for me?

585
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:07,960
'Course I have. Hello, darlin'.

586
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:09,480
Don't kill him.

587
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:12,480
You've landed on your feet
here, ain't ya?

588
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:15,000
This is Jane,
my lovely assistant.

589
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:18,000
- I talked to you on the phone?
- Yeah.

590
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:20,000
- Can I take your coats?
- Yes.

591
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:22,000
Drink? Red, white,
rose, beer?

592
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:23,520
- I'll have white.
- Beer.

593
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:25,040
Thanks a lot.

594
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:26,560
- Cynth?
- White, please.

595
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,080
- Jane?
- Rose.

596
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:29,320
Okey-doke.

597
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:33,240
- Where's the friend?
- I've no idea.

598
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:35,240
You got an ashtray, darlin'?

599
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,240
There's one on the coffee table.

600
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:40,240
I didn't think
you'd have given up.

601
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:42,760
One of the few
pleasures in life.

602
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:45,760
- These are very bright.
- Don't you like 'em?

603
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:47,800
I'll just put them in a vase.

604
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:53,600
- What's that there for?
- We like it.

605
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,120
Oi, don't laugh.

606
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:56,520
It's stupid.

607
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:58,800
[Maurice] One of my early works.

608
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:00,320
Miserable little git.

609
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:02,320
[Roxanne] You was
fuckin' around.

610
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,000
Oi, mind your language.

611
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:08,160
- How's work, then?
- It's all right, yeah.

612
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:10,040
- Still enjoying it?
- Yeah.

613
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:12,040
- When you goin' to college?
- Shut up.

614
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:13,800
- You're goin' to college.
- I ain't.

615
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:17,360
- You got a good brain.
- Don't wanna use it.

616
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,880
- Suit yourself.
- I will.

617
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,400
Paul's a scaffolder.

618
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:21,880
Yeah, your mum said.

619
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,360
Bet that's hard work.

620
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:24,880
It can be, mate.

621
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,480
- Especially in the winter.
- That's right.

622
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:32,520
I wanted to give it
a Mediterranean feel.

623
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:34,040
It's a lovely kitchen.

624
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:36,040
- And this is... Oops!
- A big lavatory.

625
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:37,560
The downstairs toilet.

626
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,560
Handy if you're in the garden.

627
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,080
It's really convenient.

628
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:44,080
I think the peach tones
make it quite tranquil.

629
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,280
Yeah.

630
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:48,280
So you know where it is
if you need it.

631
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:49,800
Now... Excuse me, Jane.

632
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,320
This is the garage.

633
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:53,320
I thought it was a cupboard!

634
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:56,320
- Is that a new car?
- Yes, that's my car.

635
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:58,280
What was wrong
with your other one?

636
00:33:58,400 --> 00:33:59,320
Nothing.

637
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:00,880
I'll show you upstairs.

638
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:08,080
We'll start with this.

639
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:10,240
Oh.

640
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,840
There's the tank.

641
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:14,080
Where I keep towels
and bedlinen.

642
00:34:14,200 --> 00:34:15,360
Your airing cupboard.

643
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:16,880
Mm. Not very capacious.

644
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,400
This is Maurice's bathroom.

645
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:20,400
It's green. Matches your tank.

646
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:23,400
These all new carpets,
are they, sweetheart?

647
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:24,840
Oh, yes.

648
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:28,280
And this is the master bedroom.

649
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,800
It's more like the bridal suite!

650
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,200
It's beautiful!

651
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:34,200
I've always wanted
a four-poster.

652
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:37,200
I can see Maurice
thrashing about in there(!)

653
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:38,720
It is a king-size.

654
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:40,720
It's out of a fairy tale.

655
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:43,720
- Bet this cost a bob or two.
- It wasn't cheap.

656
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,240
And here's another lavatory.

657
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:47,760
That bathroom's mine.
The en-suite.

658
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:50,760
You've got one each?
Nice, ain't it, Jane?

659
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:52,280
It's like a hotel.

660
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:55,280
Don't want to
trip over each other.

661
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:57,800
Oh, you've got
everything, Monica.

662
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:00,360
- So where's this friend?
- He's here.

663
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:03,520
- No. Your mum's.
- What you talkin' about?

664
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:06,480
She asked if she could
bring a friend from work.

665
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:08,760
- First I've heard.
- Is it?

666
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,760
- She never mentioned it?
- No.

667
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:12,200
Peculiar.

668
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:15,720
That must be who
she's been goin' out with.

669
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,760
She's a dark horse, ain't she?

670
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,200
- Hello.
- No, I'm sorry...

671
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:25,200
I'm a friend of Cynthia's.

672
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,720
Yes. Yes, of course.

673
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:28,240
Hello, sweetheart!

674
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:30,760
- Hello.
- I thought you were, uh...

675
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:32,280
Come on in.

676
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:33,800
That's me mate, Hortense.

677
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,000
Hi.

678
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:36,520
That's me brother's wife.

679
00:35:36,640 --> 00:35:38,040
Pleased to meet you.

680
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:39,560
- Monica.
- Hello, Monica.

681
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:41,600
Come on out the back,
meet me brother.

682
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:43,080
OK.

683
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:45,080
Can I take your coat...?

684
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:46,720
- Hortense.
- Hortense.

685
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,400
- Hortense.
- Thank you.

686
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,880
This is me little
brother, Maurice.

687
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,880
Pleased to meet you, Maurice.

688
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:57,400
Ain't that little.
That's Hortense.

689
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:58,920
- Hortense.
- Yeah, that's right.

690
00:35:59,040 --> 00:36:01,440
And this is
me daughter, Roxanne.

691
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,960
Oh, happy birthday.

692
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:05,920
Oh, you didn't have to
do that, sweetheart.

693
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,360
It's OK.

694
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:10,880
- That's Paul, her intended.
- He ain't me intended.

695
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:12,400
And this is, um...

696
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:13,920
- Jane.
- Maurice's assistant.

697
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:15,920
- Hi.
- Very nice to meet you.

698
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:17,440
That's nice, innit?

699
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:19,960
- Drink? Red, white, rose?
- White, please.

700
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:21,480
Thanks. That's really nice.

701
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:22,880
You're welcome.

702
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:25,400
- We'll have it later.
- No, don't waste it.

703
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:27,920
I've got some to have
with the cake.

704
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,920
We thought you'd got lost.

705
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:31,920
I took a few wrong turns.

706
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:33,920
- In a minicab?
- She's got a car.

707
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:35,440
- Thanks.
- There you go.

708
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:36,960
Who wants a top up?

709
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:38,960
- I'll have one.
- Not for me.

710
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:41,480
Would you like
a crisp, Hortense?

711
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:43,000
No, I'm fine. Thanks.

712
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:46,520
I only met Paul for
the first time today, Hortense.

713
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:48,520
- He's a scaffolder.
- Are you?

714
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:50,520
Another one bites the dust.

715
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,520
That must be quite dangerous.

716
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:54,040
Well, it can be.

717
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,040
Come and lollop over here.

718
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:58,040
D'you go up really high?

719
00:36:58,160 --> 00:36:59,200
Sometimes.

720
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:02,760
Just you and
the elements, really.

721
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:04,280
Ever fallen off?

722
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,280
Would you like a crudite?

723
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,040
- Thank you, no.
- Oh, well.

724
00:37:08,160 --> 00:37:10,040
- You work with my mum?
- Yeah.

725
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:11,560
- On the machines?
- No.

726
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,560
Comin' round
tomorrow night, Paul?

727
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:14,760
- Mum!
- Well...

728
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:16,280
- Eh?
- We're goin' out.

729
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:19,800
You'll come and have
a drink? It's her 21st.

730
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:21,320
It's no big deal.

731
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:24,320
- I ain't give you your present.
- Chicken drumsticks.

732
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:26,800
- D'you want some salad?
- Yes, please.

733
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:28,320
I'll get you some.

734
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:30,840
Doing something special
tomorrow night?

735
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:32,840
No. Down the pub, as usual.

736
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:36,320
- Can we use fingers?
- Use your feet if you want.

737
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:39,320
- You've a knife and fork, Jane.
- Bit late now.

738
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:41,320
What d'you do at the factory?

739
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:44,320
- This looks lovely.
- Hope it don't kill ya.

740
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,320
- You ain't her boss?
- No.

741
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:48,320
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

742
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:50,320
- Some salad, Paul?
- No, thanks.

743
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:53,320
- It's good for you.
- He don't want none.

744
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:56,320
What about Jane?
Does she want salad?

745
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,840
Ta very much.

746
00:37:57,960 --> 00:37:59,840
What do you do, Roxanne?

747
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:01,840
I work for the council.

748
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:04,840
- Down the dole?
- No, I'm a road sweeper.

749
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:06,360
Who's for a potato?

750
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:08,880
- She's got my plate.
- Here you are.

751
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:10,280
- Hortense?
- Please.

752
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:12,280
- I'll have some of that.
- Please.

753
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:14,800
You DO get girl road sweepers.

754
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,800
- Burgers and bangers.
- Nice one.

755
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,320
That's your one, Roxanne.

756
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:21,320
With your name on it.
The burnt one.

757
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:23,320
- Potato for you, Paul?
- Please.

758
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:24,840
A nice big one.

759
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:27,360
- Here, darlin'.
- One for you, pet?

760
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:29,360
Shall I do YOU, Monica?

761
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,360
I'll see to myself. Sit down.

762
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:34,360
What about Maurice?
Who's lookin' after the worker?

763
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:37,360
Don't worry about me.
I'll eat in a minute.

764
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:38,880
Your potato's there, Cynthia.

765
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:40,880
I think I'LL have salad.

766
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:42,880
Can I have my tongs back?

767
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:44,880
- Got butter?
- Yes. Just a minute.

768
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,400
And mustard, Monica.

769
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:49,400
You like the American,
don't you, Roxanne?

770
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:50,800
Yeah. Ta.

771
00:38:50,920 --> 00:38:52,840
I'll just get some salad.

772
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:56,800
- Some butter, Paul?
- All right, darlin'?

773
00:38:56,920 --> 00:38:58,800
- Please.
- Waitin' for the butter.

774
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,320
- There, Cynth.
- Oh, Maurice!

775
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,840
That'll shut you up.

776
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:04,320
Having a steak,
are you, Cynthia?

777
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,840
Yes. Thank you, Monica.

778
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:08,360
That'll put hairs on your chest.

779
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:11,360
Like some mustard
or would you prefer French?

780
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:12,880
This looks lovely, Maurice.

781
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:14,080
Right.

782
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:15,600
There you go, mate.

783
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:17,120
Half a cow for you.

784
00:39:17,240 --> 00:39:19,640
- Look at the size of it!
- Ridiculous.

785
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:22,640
There's enough there
for ALL of us.

786
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,640
Put colour in your cheeks.

787
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:26,640
No-one else wants a steak?

788
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,640
- Ain't you havin' one?
- No, Cynthia.

789
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:30,640
- Not allowed.
- Mustard, Paul?

790
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:33,640
- It's lovely.
- Can't get rid of it, can you?

791
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:36,640
Oh, it's a real
communal thing, eating.

792
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:37,800
Yes.

793
