- What's that?

897
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:39,880
- Book token.
- Don't be stupid!

898
00:43:43,640 --> 00:43:45,040
Fuckin' hell, Maurice.

899
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:46,240
[Roxanne] Thanks!

900
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:48,600
- Your 21st, innit?
- Thanks, Monica.

901
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:51,160
Happy birthday, pet.

902
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,920
Don't spend it all
in the one shop.

903
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:55,440
Here, happy birthday.

904
00:43:55,560 --> 00:43:58,200
Wish I'd brought
MY present with me.

905
00:43:58,320 --> 00:44:01,200
Give it to her tomorrow.
That's her birthday.

906
00:44:01,320 --> 00:44:03,960
Don't expect I shall
see her tomorrow.

907
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:05,960
Gonna sit down, darlin'?

908
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:08,440
Sit down, everybody.
Have some cake.

909
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:09,640
Hortense. Jane.

910
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:12,160
[Roxanne] Where am I goin'?

911
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:14,680
[Maurice] Anywhere you like.

912
00:44:14,800 --> 00:44:18,120
- Come on the end, Paul.
- Hortense.

913
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:23,440
Where's the bathroom?

914
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:25,440
It's just through there,
sweetheart.

915
00:44:25,560 --> 00:44:29,440
[Maurice] The door straight
ahead, the light's on the left.

916
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:31,040
Thank you.

917
00:44:53,480 --> 00:44:58,160
- She's a nice girl.
- Yes, she is, Maurice.

918
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:01,000
- Seems very pleasant.
- Yeah, she's all right.

919
00:45:01,120 --> 00:45:03,160
- How you doin', Paul?
- All right.

920
00:45:03,280 --> 00:45:05,280
- Has your shirt dried off?
- Yeah.

921
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:11,600
She takes after her mother.

922
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:13,600
[Maurice] Does she?

923
00:45:13,720 --> 00:45:16,600
[Monica] You know her as well?

924
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:20,120
[Maurice] Work at
the factory, does she?

925
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:21,680
You're lookin' at her.

926
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:23,320
Eh?

927
00:45:23,440 --> 00:45:25,800
She's my daughter.

928
00:45:31,160 --> 00:45:32,840
What's the matter with ya?

929
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:34,200
Maurice...

930
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:36,760
it's me daughter.

931
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:41,120
Don't be stupid.
She's had too much to drink.

932
00:45:45,560 --> 00:45:47,480
She can't be the one that...

933
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:52,160
What?

934
00:45:54,160 --> 00:45:56,080
Hortense, sweetheart.

935
00:45:57,640 --> 00:45:59,560
She's your sister!

936
00:46:03,120 --> 00:46:04,240
What?

937
00:46:06,040 --> 00:46:08,480
That's her half-sister, Paul.

938
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:21,640
You... you eat your
cake, sweetheart.

939
00:46:21,760 --> 00:46:22,840
Thanks.

940
00:46:22,960 --> 00:46:25,400
- What's the matter?
- I'm all right.

941
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:33,040
[Cynthia] I told 'em.

942
00:46:33,160 --> 00:46:34,600
[Cynthia sobs]

943
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:41,040
[Cynthia] Tell 'em
who you are, sweetheart.

944
00:46:43,840 --> 00:46:46,720
It wasn't supposed
to happen like this.

945
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:50,000
Well, it has.
So you tell 'em, go on.

946
00:46:54,120 --> 00:46:55,520
Is it true?

947
00:46:55,640 --> 00:46:57,080
Yes, it is.

948
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:01,440
[Maurice]
You never told her, then?

949
00:47:01,560 --> 00:47:02,960
I'm sorry, darlin'.

950
00:47:03,080 --> 00:47:06,480
Will someone tell me
what the fuck's goin' on?

951
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:09,000
She's your sister!

952
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:13,040
Maurice?

953
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:17,480
Monica?

954
00:47:18,920 --> 00:47:21,840
I always said
she had a right to know.

955
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:26,600
No, Roxanne.
Sweetheart, darlin'!

956
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:29,600
- Darlin', please!
- I'll smack you, you slag!

957
00:47:29,720 --> 00:47:32,000
Ain't enough
you had one bastard,

958
00:47:32,120 --> 00:47:34,000
- you had to have two!
- Stop it!

959
00:47:34,120 --> 00:47:37,360
[Maurice] Roxanne? Roxy?

960
00:47:38,600 --> 00:47:41,040
Sit down, darlin'.
Sit down, Paul.

961
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:47,840
Cynthia, I think I should go.

962
00:47:47,960 --> 00:47:51,000
I don't want you to go.
You sit down.

963
00:47:51,120 --> 00:47:53,000
Eat your cake, Jane.

964
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:56,000
You don't half choose
your moments, Cynthia.

965
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:58,000
When's the RIGHT
moment, Maurice?

966
00:47:58,120 --> 00:48:00,000
You tell me that.

967
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:02,000
Paul, get my coat. We're goin'.

968
00:48:02,120 --> 00:48:04,000
- Don't go.
- Why didn't you tell me?

969
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:07,520
- I thought you knew.
- You used to tell me everythin'!

970
00:48:07,640 --> 00:48:10,520
- I'm sorry.
- You've fuckin' let me down!

971
00:48:10,640 --> 00:48:13,320
As for you,
you've ruined my party

972
00:48:13,440 --> 00:48:15,320
and I hope you're happy!

973
00:48:15,440 --> 00:48:16,800
Roxy... Roxanne!

974
00:48:37,120 --> 00:48:38,880
She don't mean it, darlin'.

975
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,440
She's just a little bit upset.

976
00:48:57,280 --> 00:49:00,160
- Where you goin'?
- I don't know.

977
00:49:01,680 --> 00:49:05,080
It's all been a bit
of a shock, innit?

978
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:06,760
Did you know about her?

979
00:49:06,880 --> 00:49:10,040
I always thought
she'd had a boy.

980
00:49:10,160 --> 00:49:12,040
- She's a slag.
- No, she's not.

981
00:49:12,160 --> 00:49:15,440
- She fuckin' is!
- She loves you. We all love you.

982
00:49:15,560 --> 00:49:16,960
You comin' back?

983
00:49:17,080 --> 00:49:19,400
