993
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:50,040
you turned my Maurice against me

994
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:52,560
and you turned me daughter
against me.

995
00:49:52,680 --> 00:49:55,160
You'll be havin' a go
at HER next.

996
00:49:55,280 --> 00:49:58,560
Sorry about this, Hortense.
Finished, Jane?

997
00:49:58,680 --> 00:50:00,560
Why don't you sit down?

998
00:50:00,680 --> 00:50:03,560
- You got a short memory.
- What is it now?

999
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:05,080
You'd have none of this

1000
00:50:05,200 --> 00:50:08,600
if I hadn't given Maurice
the money to start with.

1001
00:50:08,720 --> 00:50:11,120
That was your father's
insurance money.

1002
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:13,640
- It was for me and Roxanne.
- And Maurice.

1003
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:16,640
He didn't want none
till he talked to you.

1004
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:18,160
He was entitled to it!

1005
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:21,160
I went out cleanin',
took her to school,

1006
00:50:21,280 --> 00:50:24,680
- then did a full day's work.
- Didn't we know it!

1007
00:50:24,800 --> 00:50:28,680
You've done nothing but spend
his money since you met him.

1008
00:50:28,800 --> 00:50:30,680
What else do you do with money?

1009
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:33,680
At least we made
something of ourselves.

1010
00:50:33,800 --> 00:50:38,720
Haven't you just. You wanna try
bringin' up a kid on your own!

1011
00:50:44,840 --> 00:50:48,240
She can't help it.
She's never had enough love.

1012
00:50:48,360 --> 00:50:49,760
And you've never got on.

1013
00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:52,280
- That ain't my fault.
- I know.

1014
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:53,760
But she needs you.

1015
00:50:54,920 --> 00:50:57,880
- Come on.
- I don't want to.

1016
00:50:58,000 --> 00:51:00,200
What do YOU think, Paul?

1017
00:51:00,320 --> 00:51:02,200
I think he's right, darlin'.

1018
00:51:02,320 --> 00:51:05,680
- Do ya?
- Yeah.

1019
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:07,680
Well, I ain't sayin' nothin'.

1020
00:51:07,800 --> 00:51:09,200
You won't have to.

1021
00:51:09,320 --> 00:51:11,200
You just have to listen.

1022
00:51:11,320 --> 00:51:12,640
Come on.

1023
00:51:27,240 --> 00:51:29,640
[Cynthia] I'm sorry, Roxanne.

1024
00:51:29,760 --> 00:51:31,640
It just came out, darlin'.

1025
00:51:31,760 --> 00:51:34,640
I didn't mean to
spoil your party.

1026
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:37,160
- Tell her, Maurice.
- Leave her, Cynth.

1027
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:39,480
[Maurice] Just tell her
the truth.

1028
00:51:41,720 --> 00:51:43,040
Darlin'...

1029
00:51:45,720 --> 00:51:48,600
I got pregnant when I was 15...

1030
00:51:48,720 --> 00:51:52,600
and your grandad sent me
away to this place.

1031
00:51:52,720 --> 00:51:54,120
Didn't he, Maurice?

1032
00:51:54,240 --> 00:51:58,280
I didn't know she was
gonna come lookin' for me.

1033
00:51:58,400 --> 00:52:02,200
But I gotta tell you
the truth, darlin',

1034
00:52:02,320 --> 00:52:04,200
I'm glad she did.

1035
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:07,320
It ain't her fault,
sweetheart.

1036
00:52:07,440 --> 00:52:10,200
She didn't wanna hurt you,

1037
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:12,640
no more than I did.

1038
00:52:12,760 --> 00:52:14,640
You tell her, sweetheart.

1039
00:52:14,760 --> 00:52:17,640
It's true. She didn't
wanna upset you.

1040
00:52:19,720 --> 00:52:21,040
I'm sorry.

1041
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:25,640
All right?

1042
00:52:27,040 --> 00:52:29,920
She said you weren't
never gonna come back.

1043
00:52:30,040 --> 00:52:31,920
[Maurice] Who did?

1044
00:52:32,040 --> 00:52:34,360
I never said any such thing.

1045
00:52:34,480 --> 00:52:36,320
She's twisted
everything as usual.

1046
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:38,320
[Cynthia] Yes, you did.

1047
00:52:38,440 --> 00:52:39,840
Well, you was wrong,

1048
00:52:39,960 --> 00:52:43,080
'cause she has come back,
ain't you, sweetheart?

1049
00:52:43,200 --> 00:52:45,520
I always thought
you should've known.

1050
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:48,040
[Maurice] You should've
told her.

1051
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:50,560
[Cynthia] 'Course I should've.

1052
00:52:50,680 --> 00:52:53,040
But I didn't think
there'd be no need.

1053
00:52:53,160 --> 00:52:55,520
You seem to have told
all and sundry.

1054
00:52:55,640 --> 00:52:58,920
Meaning me, I suppose.
I am his wife, after all.

1055
00:52:59,040 --> 00:53:01,920
[Cynthia]
Then behave like his wife.

1056
00:53:02,040 --> 00:53:05,000
- Why ain't you give him no kids?
- Quiet, Cynthia.

1057
00:53:05,120 --> 00:53:07,000
That's between Maurice and me.

1058
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:10,280
You might not have
wanted 'em but HE did.

1059
00:53:10,400 --> 00:53:12,040
- Shut up!
- You know nothing.

1060
00:53:12,160 --> 00:53:14,080
- Don't I?
- There are things...

1061
00:53:14,200 --> 00:53:15,720
- Maurice.
- Like what?

1062
00:53:21,360 --> 00:53:22,800
Tell her.

1063
00:53:26,520 --> 00:53:28,520
Tell me what?

1064
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:32,000
Why can't you tell her?

1065
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:39,880
She can't have kids.

1066
00:53:41,040 --> 00:53:42,440
Simple as that.

1067
00:53:42,560 --> 00:53:44,360
She's physically incapable...

1068
00:53:44,480 --> 00:53:45,880
of havin' children.

1069
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:48,280
[Maurice] We've had every test

1070
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:50,280
known to medical science.

1071
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:53,280
She's been prodded,
poked, had operations.

1072
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:55,280
We've had 15 years of it

1073
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:57,280
and she can't have a baby.

1074
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:59,280
I love you to bits...

1075
00:53:59,400 --> 00:54:02,240
but it's almost destroyed
our relationship.

1076
00:54:03,400 --> 00:54:04,840
You know it has.

1077
00:54:08,120 --> 00:54:09,240
There.

1078
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:12,240
I've said it.

1079
00:54:13,800 --> 00:54:16,360
So where's the bolt
of lightnin'?

1080
00:54:19,680 --> 00:54:21,600
Secrets and lies!

1081
00:54:23,160 --> 00:54:25,040
We're ALL in pain.

1082
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:27,560
Why can't we SHARE our pain?

1083
00:54:27,680 --> 00:54:31,560
I've spent my entire life
tryin' to make people happy!

1084
00:54:31,680 --> 00:54:35,560
And the three people
I love the most in the world

1085
00:54:35,680 --> 00:54:39,000
hate each other's guts!
I'm in the middle -

1086
00:54:39,120 --> 00:54:41,040
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANY MORE!

1087
00:54:48,400 --> 00:54:50,400
I'm sorry, Hortense.

1088
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:52,800
But you are a very brave person.

1089
00:54:52,920 --> 00:54:55,800
- A very stupid person.
- No, you're not.

1090
00:54:55,920 --> 00:54:57,800
You wanted to find the truth

1091
00:54:57,920 --> 00:55:00,800
and you were prepared
to suffer the consequences.

1092
00:55:00,920 --> 00:55:02,760
And I admire you for that.

1093
00:55:03,920 --> 00:55:05,360
I mean it.

1094
00:55:42,800 --> 00:55:45,240
You're so lucky, Cynthia.

1095
00:55:59,120 --> 00:56:02,000
Have you really been
working in the factory?

1096
00:56:02,120 --> 00:56:03,160
No.

1097
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:05,720
What d'you do, then?

1098
00:56:05,840 --> 00:56:07,280
I'm an optometrist.

1099
00:56:11,720 --> 00:56:13,640
Welcome to the family.

1100
00:56:17,760 --> 00:56:19,160
[Jane sobs]

1101
00:56:19,280 --> 00:56:20,360
Maurice...

1102
00:56:20,480 --> 00:56:23,320
I wish I'd had a dad like you.

1103
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,160
You're lovely!

1104
00:56:36,280 --> 00:56:38,680
His name's... Bingham.

1105
00:56:38,800 --> 00:56:40,240
Your father.

1106
00:56:42,800 --> 00:56:45,240
[Cynthia] He's from America.

1107
00:56:47,200 --> 00:56:49,080
I met him on holiday.

1108
00:56:49,200 --> 00:56:50,240
Benidorm.

1109
00:56:51,400 --> 00:56:53,320
He's a medical student.

1110
00:56:54,880 --> 00:56:58,800
One morning, I come down
and he weren't there no more.

1111
00:57:01,280 --> 00:57:03,200
But he was a nice man.

1112
00:57:05,760 --> 00:57:07,200
He was.

1113
00:57:15,720 --> 00:57:17,640
Was MY father a "nice man"?

1114
00:57:19,200 --> 00:57:22,120
Oh, don't break
my heart, darlin'!

1115
00:57:48,520 --> 00:57:49,960
I'm all right.

1116
00:57:51,520 --> 00:57:53,440
[Cynthia sobs loudly]

1117
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:10,640
Oh, PLEASE, Roxanne, sweetheart!

1118
00:58:10,760 --> 00:58:12,080
PLEASE!

1119
00:58:22,720 --> 00:58:24,160
I'm frightened.

1120
00:58:26,120 --> 00:58:27,240
Why?

1121
00:58:29,720 --> 00:58:31,640
You don't love me
any more.

1122
00:58:34,520 --> 00:58:36,440
Not like you used to.

1123
00:58:39,120 --> 00:58:40,440
Maurice!

1124
00:58:46,120 --> 00:58:49,040
You don't know
how MUCH I love you.

1125
00:58:50,720 --> 00:58:52,040
Do you?

1126
00:59:05,720 --> 00:59:08,160
We've got each other,
haven't we?

1127
00:59:23,320 --> 00:59:26,760
Bet you've never seen
so much shit, have you?

1128
00:59:26,880 --> 00:59:28,760
You wanna see my mum's house!

1129
00:59:28,880 --> 00:59:30,240
D'you miss her?

1130
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:32,760
Yeah.

1131
00:59:32,880 --> 00:59:37,000
- Did you get on with her?
- She used to drive me mad!

1132
00:59:37,120 --> 00:59:38,600
That's what they're
there for, ain't it?

1133
00:59:38,720 --> 00:59:40,000
Yeah.

1134
00:59:40,120 --> 00:59:42,000
That's me old chair, there.

1135
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,200
Aw.

1136
00:59:43,320 --> 00:59:45,880
I always wanted
a little sister.

1137
00:59:47,400 --> 00:59:50,280
It's just my brothers
were much older than me

1138
00:59:50,400 --> 00:59:53,280
so I ended up
playing on my own.

1139
00:59:53,400 --> 00:59:55,320
Oh, I know what you mean.

1140
00:59:57,720 --> 00:59:59,600
[Hortense giggles]

1141
00:59:59,720 --> 01:00:01,160
What you laughin' at?

1142
01:00:04,520 --> 01:00:06,920
Do you feel like we're sisters?

1143
01:00:07,040 --> 01:00:08,320
I dunno.

1144
01:00:08,440 --> 01:00:09,800
Do you?

1145
01:00:12,720 --> 01:00:14,600
- It's a bit weird.
- Yeah.

1146
01:00:14,720 --> 01:00:16,600
I don't mind it, though.

1147
01:00:16,720 --> 01:00:18,120
No. Nor do I.

1148
01:00:18,240 --> 01:00:21,120
Don't even know you yet, do I?

1149
01:00:21,240 --> 01:00:23,120
D'you wanna go out one night?

1150
01:00:23,240 --> 01:00:24,320
Yeah.

1151
01:00:24,440 --> 01:00:25,520
Yeah.

1152
01:00:25,640 --> 01:00:28,520
You can take me
to one of your pubs.

1153
01:00:28,640 --> 01:00:30,080
Yeah, all right.

1154
01:00:31,640 --> 01:00:33,480
How would you introduce me?

1155
01:00:34,640 --> 01:00:36,040
As your half-sister?

1156
01:00:36,160 --> 01:00:37,280
Yeah.

1157
01:00:38,840 --> 01:00:41,720
No, man. Too much
explaining to do.

1158
01:00:41,840 --> 01:00:44,240
- It's what I'd say, though.
- Would ya?

1159
01:00:44,360 --> 01:00:45,440
Yeah.

1160
01:00:45,560 --> 01:00:48,440
Yeah. Best to tell
the truth, innit?

1161
01:00:48,560 --> 01:00:49,960
Yeah, it is.

1162
01:00:50,080 --> 01:00:52,000
That way, nobody gets hurt.

1163
01:00:55,120 --> 01:00:58,040
Here you are, sweetheart.
Tea's up!

1164
01:00:59,600 --> 01:01:01,000
Go on, darlin'.

1165
01:01:01,120 --> 01:01:04,000
- Want a biscuit?
- No, I'm all right.

1166
01:01:04,120 --> 01:01:05,560
Sit yourself down.

1167
01:01:05,680 --> 01:01:08,080
- You all right with that?
- Yeah.

1168
01:01:08,200 --> 01:01:09,520
That's it.

1169
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:17,440
Who'd have thought it, eh?

1170
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:20,880
Look at you two sittin' there -

1171
01:01:21,000 --> 01:01:22,880
like a couple of garden gnomes!

1172
01:01:23,000 --> 01:01:24,920
[Cynthia chuckles]

1173
01:01:29,120 --> 01:01:31,000
Oh, this is the life, eh?

1174
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:33,040
[Roxanne and Hortense] Yeah.

